#: ../../library/decimal.rst:33
msgid ""
"The :mod:`!decimal` module provides support for fast correctly rounded "
"decimal floating-point arithmetic. It offers several advantages over the :"
"class:`float` datatype:"
msgstr ""
"O mĂłdulo :mod:`!decimal` fornece suporte Ă  aritmĂ©tica rĂĄpida de ponto "
"flutuante decimal, com arredondamento correto. Oferece vĂĄrias vantagens "
"sobre o tipo de dados :class:`float`:"

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:37
msgid ""
"Decimal \"is based on a `floating-point model <https://speleotrove.com/"
"decimal/damodel.html#refnumber>`__ which was designed with people in mind, "
"and necessarily has a paramount guiding principle -- computers must provide "
"an arithmetic that works in the same way as the arithmetic that people learn "
"at school.\" -- excerpt from the decimal arithmetic specification."
msgstr ""
"Decimal \"Ă© baseado em um `modelo de ponto flutuante <https://speleotrove."
"com/decimal/damodel.html#refnumber>`__ que foi projetado com as pessoas em "
"mente e necessariamente tem um princĂ­pio orientador primordial -- os "
"computadores devem fornecer uma aritmĂ©tica que funcione da mesma maneira que "
"a aritmĂ©tica que as pessoas aprendem na escola\". -- Trecho da especificaĂ§ĂŁo "
"aritmĂ©tica decimal."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:44
msgid ""
"Decimal numbers can be represented exactly.  In contrast, numbers like "
"``1.1`` and ``2.2`` do not have exact representations in binary floating "
"point. End users typically would not expect ``1.1 + 2.2`` to display as "
"``3.3000000000000003`` as it does with binary floating point."
msgstr ""
"Os nĂșmeros decimais podem ser representados exatamente. Por outro lado, "
"nĂșmeros como ``1.1`` e ``2.2`` nĂŁo tĂȘm representaĂ§Ă”es exatas em ponto "
"flutuante binĂĄrio. Os usuĂĄrios finais normalmente nĂŁo esperam que ``1.1 + "
"2.2`` sejam exibidos como ``3.3000000000000003``, como ocorre com o ponto "
"flutuante binĂĄrio."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:49
msgid ""
"The exactness carries over into arithmetic.  In decimal floating point, "
"``0.1 + 0.1 + 0.1 - 0.3`` is exactly equal to zero.  In binary floating "
"point, the result is ``5.5511151231257827e-017``.  While near to zero, the "
"differences prevent reliable equality testing and differences can "
"accumulate. For this reason, decimal is preferred in accounting applications "
"which have strict equality invariants."
msgstr ""
"A exatidĂŁo transita para a aritmĂ©tica. No ponto flutuante decimal, ``0.1 + "
"0.1 + 0.1 - 0.3`` Ă© exatamente igual a zero. No ponto flutuante binĂĄrio, o "
"resultado Ă© ``5.5511151231257827e-017``. Embora prĂłximas de zero, as "
"diferenĂ§as impedem o teste de igualdade confiĂĄvel, e podem se acumular. Por "
"esse motivo, o decimal Ă© preferido em aplicaĂ§Ă”es de contabilidade que "
"envolvem invariĂĄveis estritos de igualdade."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:56
msgid ""
"The decimal module incorporates a notion of significant places so that "
"``1.30 + 1.20`` is ``2.50``.  The trailing zero is kept to indicate "
"significance. This is the customary presentation for monetary applications. "
"For multiplication, the \"schoolbook\" approach uses all the figures in the "
"multiplicands.  For instance, ``1.3 * 1.2`` gives ``1.56`` while ``1.30 * "
"1.20`` gives ``1.5600``."
msgstr ""
"O mĂłdulo decimal incorpora uma noĂ§ĂŁo de casas significativas para que ``1.30 "
"+ 1.20`` seja ``2.50``. O zero Ă  direita Ă© mantido para indicar "
"significĂąncia. Esta Ă© a apresentaĂ§ĂŁo habitual para aplicaĂ§Ă”es monetĂĄrias. "
"Para multiplicaĂ§ĂŁo, a abordagem \"livro escolar\" usa todas as figuras nos "
"multiplicandos. Por exemplo, ``1.3 * 1.2`` Ă© igual a ``1.56`` enquanto "
"``1.30 * 1.20`` Ă© igual a ``1.5600``."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:63
msgid ""
"Unlike hardware based binary floating point, the decimal module has a user "
"alterable precision (defaulting to 28 places) which can be as large as "
"needed for a given problem:"
msgstr ""
"Diferentemente do ponto flutuante binĂĄrio baseado em hardware, o mĂłdulo "
"decimal possui uma precisĂŁo alterĂĄvel pelo usuĂĄrio (padrĂŁo de 28 casas), que "
"pode ser tĂŁo grande quanto necessĂĄrio para um determinado problema:"

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:75
msgid ""
"Both binary and decimal floating point are implemented in terms of published "
"standards.  While the built-in float type exposes only a modest portion of "
"its capabilities, the decimal module exposes all required parts of the "
"standard. When needed, the programmer has full control over rounding and "
"signal handling. This includes an option to enforce exact arithmetic by "
"using exceptions to block any inexact operations."
msgstr ""
"O ponto flutuante binĂĄrio e decimal Ă© implementado em termos de padrĂ”es "
"publicados. Enquanto o tipo ponto flutuante embutido expĂ”e apenas uma parte "
"modesta de seus recursos, o mĂłdulo decimal expĂ”e todas as partes necessĂĄrias "
"do padrĂŁo. Quando necessĂĄrio, o programador tem controle total sobre o "
"arredondamento e o manuseio do sinal. Isso inclui uma opĂ§ĂŁo para impor "
"aritmĂ©tica exata usando exceĂ§Ă”es para bloquear quaisquer operaĂ§Ă”es inexatas."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:82
msgid ""
"The decimal module was designed to support \"without prejudice, both exact "
"unrounded decimal arithmetic (sometimes called fixed-point arithmetic) and "
"rounded floating-point arithmetic.\"  -- excerpt from the decimal arithmetic "
"specification."
msgstr ""
"O mĂłdulo decimal foi projetado para dar suporte, \"sem prejuĂ­zo, Ă  "
"aritmĂ©tica decimal nĂŁo arredondada exata (Ă s vezes chamada de aritmĂ©tica de "
"ponto fixo) e Ă  aritmĂ©tica arredondada de ponto flutuante\". -- Trecho da "
"especificaĂ§ĂŁo aritmĂ©tica decimal."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:87
msgid ""
"The module design is centered around three concepts:  the decimal number, "
"the context for arithmetic, and signals."
msgstr ""
"O design do mĂłdulo Ă© centrado em torno de trĂȘs conceitos: o nĂșmero decimal, "
"o contexto da aritmĂ©tica e os sinais."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:90
msgid ""
"A decimal number is immutable.  It has a sign, coefficient digits, and an "
"exponent.  To preserve significance, the coefficient digits do not truncate "
"trailing zeros.  Decimals also include special values such as ``Infinity``, "
"``-Infinity``, and ``NaN``.  The standard also differentiates ``-0`` from "
"``+0``."
msgstr ""
"Um nĂșmero decimal Ă© imutĂĄvel. Possui um sinal, dĂ­gitos de coeficiente e um "
"expoente. Para preservar a significĂąncia, os dĂ­gitos do coeficiente nĂŁo "
"truncam zeros Ă  direita. Os decimais tambĂ©m incluem valores especiais, tais "
"como ``Infinity``, ``-Infinity`` e ``NaN``. O padrĂŁo tambĂ©m diferencia "
"``-0`` de ``+0``."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:96
msgid ""
"The context for arithmetic is an environment specifying precision, rounding "
"rules, limits on exponents, flags indicating the results of operations, and "
"trap enablers which determine whether signals are treated as exceptions.  "
"Rounding options include :const:`ROUND_CEILING`, :const:`ROUND_DOWN`, :const:"
"`ROUND_FLOOR`, :const:`ROUND_HALF_DOWN`, :const:`ROUND_HALF_EVEN`, :const:"
"`ROUND_HALF_UP`, :const:`ROUND_UP`, and :const:`ROUND_05UP`."
msgstr ""
"O contexto da aritmĂ©tica Ă© um ambiente que especifica precisĂŁo, regras de "
"arredondamento, limites de expoentes, sinalizadores indicando os resultados "
"das operaĂ§Ă”es e ativadores de interceptaĂ§ĂŁo que determinam se os sinais sĂŁo "
"tratados como exceĂ§Ă”es. As opĂ§Ă”es de arredondamento incluem :const:"
"`ROUND_CEILING`, :const:`ROUND_DOWN`, :const:`ROUND_FLOOR`, :const:"
"`ROUND_HALF_DOWN`, :const:`ROUND_HALF_EVEN`, :const:`ROUND_HALF_UP`, :const:"
"`ROUND_UP` e :const:`ROUND_05UP`."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:103
msgid ""
"Signals are groups of exceptional conditions arising during the course of "
"computation.  Depending on the needs of the application, signals may be "
"ignored, considered as informational, or treated as exceptions. The signals "
"in the decimal module are: :const:`Clamped`, :const:`InvalidOperation`, :"
"const:`DivisionByZero`, :const:`Inexact`, :const:`Rounded`, :const:"
"`Subnormal`, :const:`Overflow`, :const:`Underflow` and :const:"
"`FloatOperation`."
msgstr ""
"Sinais sĂŁo grupos de condiĂ§Ă”es excepcionais que surgem durante o curso da "
"computaĂ§ĂŁo. Dependendo das necessidades da aplicaĂ§ĂŁo, os sinais podem ser "
"ignorados, considerados informativos ou tratados como exceĂ§Ă”es. Os sinais no "
"mĂłdulo decimal sĂŁo: :const:`Clamped`, :const:`InvalidOperation`, :const:"
"`DivisionByZero`, :const:`Inexact`, :const:`Rounded`, :const:`Subnormal`, :"
"const:`Overflow`, :const:`Underflow` e :const:`FloatOperation`."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:110
msgid ""
"For each signal there is a flag and a trap enabler.  When a signal is "
"encountered, its flag is set to one, then, if the trap enabler is set to "
"one, an exception is raised.  Flags are sticky, so the user needs to reset "
"them before monitoring a calculation."
msgstr ""
"Para cada sinal, hĂĄ um sinalizador e um ativador de interceptaĂ§ĂŁo. Quando um "
"sinal Ă© encontrado, seu sinalizador Ă© definido como um e, se o ativador de "
"interceptaĂ§ĂŁo estiver definido como um, uma exceĂ§ĂŁo serĂĄ gerada. Os "
"sinalizadores sĂŁo fixos; portanto, o usuĂĄrio precisa redefini-los antes de "
"monitorar um cĂĄlculo."

#: ../../library/decimal.rst:118
msgid ""
"IBM's General Decimal Arithmetic Specification, `The General Decimal "
"Arithmetic Specification <https://speleotrove.com/decimal/decarith.html>`_."
msgstr ""
"A especificaĂ§ĂŁo geral aritmĂ©tica decimal da IBM, `The General Decimal "
